substep.action:
Output this format (substitute milestone data from the file):

🎯 MENTOR OVERVIEW: The Founder Journey

6 milestones from idea to MVP:
  M1: {name} — {goal}
  M2: {name} — {goal}
  M3: {name} — {goal}
  M4: {name} — {goal}
  M5: {name} — {goal}
  M6: {name} — {goal}

→ Use [N] to start a new project or [C] to continue an existing one.

Output this format (display MUST NOT exceed 15 lines):

🎯 YOU ARE HERE: {projectName}

{all-milestones line from 3c2, with milestone names}

Milestone: M{N} {milestoneName} ({done}/{total} in this milestone)
  {marker} [{code}] {frameworkName}
  ... (one line per framework, indented under milestone, FRAMEWORK ROUTING order)

Progress: {done}/{total} complete

Available: [M{N}] Continue {milestoneName} | [PM] Party Mode

When codes are unavailable (M5/M6 fallback), omit the [{code}] prefix:
  {marker} {frameworkName}
